Recommender Systems project part2 -- 2025 -- Mikko Eerola

Using part1 init and recommender function make group member recommendations lists. Using these full lists and considering
only top20 predicted movies from each users we build a candidate list of movies for the sqeuntial recommendations.

The 'new' sequential group recommender design combines balancing satisfaction method with squirrel ML framework of pleasing
the most disagreeing member when group disagreenment is high. This is done as follows:

Considering seq. rec. S_i at i round of recommendations. The next movie j is chosen to S_i+1 so that the score is maximized.
The score is defined as: a * satO(S_i+1) + b * groupDisagreenment(S_i+1).

where a and b are balancing scalars by default a=0.7 and 0.3. This means that overall satisfaction is prioritized first.
After adding j to recommendations list S_i+1, the groupDisagreenment is over 0.5 next item is selected with adjusted scalars
(a=0.3 and b=0-7). This process is continued untill we have 5 sequential recommendations for the group.

This process balances the satisfaction and disagreenment and works like a light version of the machine learning version.
In the final list of seqeuntial recommendations the predicted rating is the avergare prediction between the group.

The program should be run in the folder where the MovieLens data FOLDER is in. The program reads csv file with path "./ml-100k/u.*".
The projectpart1.py file should be in the same folder than the main file projectpart2.py file.

root
--part2
----projectpart1.py
----projectpart2.py
--ml-100k
----u.*
----...
So in working directory/root run: python .\part2\projectpart2.py